{"type":"message","id":"a7f5d67e","parentId":"e90d5dc0","timestamp":"2026-03-03T13:35:19.671Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Excellent! The API works with \"parameters\" instead of \"params\"! Now I got the Finnhub news data. The data doesn't seem to have a \"heat\" field though. Let me look at the structure - it has category, datetime, headline, id, image, related, source, summary, url.\n\nThe user asked for \"热度≥80\" which likely means they want news with high engagement/popularity. The Finnhub API doesn't seem to provide a heat score directly. Let me check if there's a way to get that information or if I need to use another approach.\n\nActually, looking more closely at the request - maybe the user is referring to some kind of热度 metric that Finnhub provides. Let me see if there's more data or another endpoint that provides heat/popularity scores.\n\nFor now, let me see what news we got and try to assess which ones might be \"hot\" based on the source and headlines. The news is from MarketWatch, CNBC etc. \n\nLet me search for a different API that might provide heat/popularity scores, or try to understand what the user means by \"热度\". In Chinese financial contexts, 热度 often refers to popularity/engagement metrics.","thinkingSignature":"64a824e76e7b669cf89f7f79d02778f07af110948f39b47fb669f0fc0f3b2e38"},{"type":"text","text":"Got the Finnhub news! The issue was using `parameters` instead of `params`. However, I notice Finnhub's news doesn't have a \"heat\" (热度) field. Let me search for an API that provides news popularity metrics:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9qqkfzi7tk0f_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/lynch/.openclaw/workspace && node scripts/qveris_tool.mjs search \"news popularity heat engagement metrics\" --limit 10","timeout":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":32105,"output":361,"cacheRead":13984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46450,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772544898157}}
{"type":"message","id":"709f27c2","parentId":"a7f5d67e","timestamp":"2026-03-03T13:35:22.041Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9qqkfzi7tk0f_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"news popularity heat engagement metrics\",\n  \"total\": 10,\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"qveris_social.x_account_hottest_post_v1\",\n      \"name\": \"X Account Hottest Post (7 Days)\",\n      \"description\": \"Return the single hottest post (by engagement) from a given X/Twitter account in the last 7 days.\",\n      \"params\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"username\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"X/Twitter username (without @)\",\n            \"zh\": \"X账号用户名（不含@）\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"account\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Alias for username\",\n            \"zh\": \"同 username\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"provider_description\": \"Social media monitoring and analysis skills\",\n      \"skill_package_url\": \"https://qveris.ai/api/v1/skills/qveris_social.x_account_hottest_post_v1/package\",\n      \"skill_type\": \"package\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"qveris_social.x_domain_hot_topics_v1\",\n      \"name\": \"X Domain Hot Topics Tracker\",\n      \"description\": \"Track and aggregate hot topics from domain experts (KOLs) on X/Twitter platform. Supports multiple domains: AI, Finance, Crypto, Tech, etc.\",\n      \"params\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"domains\",\n          \"type\": \"array\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"List of domains to query. Available: AI, Finance, Crypto, Tech, Science. If not specified, queries all domains.\",\n            \"zh\": \"要查询的领域列表。可选：AI、Finance、Crypto、Tech、Science。如不指定则查询所有领域。\"\n          },\n          \"enum\": [\n            \"AI\",\n            \"Finance\",\n            \"Crypto\",\n            \"Tech\",\n            \"Science\"\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"limit\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Maximum number of results to return per domain\",\n            \"zh\": \"每个领域返回结果的最大数量\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"min_engagement\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Minimum engagement (likes + retweets + replies) for filtering posts\",\n            \"zh\": \"用于过滤的最小互动量（点赞+转发+回复）\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"provider_description\": \"Social media monitoring and analysis skills\",\n      \"skill_package_url\": \"https://qveris.ai/api/v1/skills/qveris_social.x_domain_hot_topics_v1/package\",\n      \"skill_type\": \"package\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"qveris_social.x_domain_new_posts_v1\",\n      \"name\": \"X Domain New Posts Today\",\n      \"description\": \"Search today's new posts from domain experts (KOLs) on X/Twitter with full fields: text, images, media, metrics. Supports AI, Finance, Crypto, Tech, Science.\",\n      \"params\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"domains\",\n          \"type\": \"array\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Domains to query\",\n            \"zh\": \"要查询的领域\"\n          },\n          \"enum\": [\n            \"AI\",\n            \"Finance\",\n            \"Crypto\",\n            \"Tech\",\n            \"Science\"\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"limit\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": null\n        }\n      ],\n      \"provider_description\": \"Social media monitoring and analysis skills\",\n      \"skill_package_url\": \"https://qveris.ai/api/v1/skills/qveris_social.x_domain_new_posts_v1/package\",\n      \"skill_type\": \"package\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"qveris_social.x_domain_hot_events_v1\",\n      \"name\": \"X Domain Hot Events Today\",\n      \"description\": \"Summarize today's hot events on X/Twitter for a domain: fetch new posts then use LLM to summarize events and return event list with post ids.\",\n      \"params\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"domains\",\n          \"type\": \"array\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Domain(s) to summarize\",\n            \"zh\": \"要总结的领域\"\n          },\n          \"enum\": [\n            \"AI\",\n            \"Finance\",\n            \"Crypto\",\n            \"Tech\",\n            \"Science\"\n          ]\n        }\n      ],\n      \"provider_description\": \"Social media monitoring and analysis skills\",\n      \"skill_package_url\": \"https://qveris.ai/api/v1/skills/qveris_social.x_domain_hot_events_v1/package\",\n      \"skill_type\": \"package\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"new_york_times_api.mostpopular.shared_articles_by_type.list.v2.aa084e50\",\n      \"name\": \"List Most Shared Articles by Share Type\",\n      \"description\": \"Returns an array of the most shared articles by share type (e.g., facebook) on NYTimes.com for a specified period of time (1 day, 7 days, or 30 days).\",\n      \"params\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"period\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Time period for which to retrieve most shared articles.\"\n          },\n          \"enum\": [\n            \"1\",\n            \"7\",\n            \"30\"\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"share_type\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"The social media platform or sharing method.\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"examples\": {\n        \"sample_parameters\": {\n          \"period\": \"1\",\n          \"share_type\": \"facebook\"\n        }\n      },\n      \"provider_description\": \"从Excel导入的Provider: New York Times API\",\n      \"stats\": {\n        \"avg_execution_time_ms\": 0,\n        \"success_rate\": 0\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"dataforseo.trends.demography.retrieve.v3.d55b490d\",\n      \"name\": \"DataForSEO Trends API - Demography Endpoint\",\n      \"description\": \"Provides a breakdown of keyword popularity by age and gender demographics.\",\n      \"examples\": {\n        \"sample_parameters\": {\n          \"keywords\": [\n            \"SEO\",\n            \"machine learning\"\n          ]\n        }\n      },\n      \"provider_description\": \"DataForSEO provides a comprehensive suite of APIs for SEO, keyword research, SERP data, backlinks, reviews, app stores, business listings, and more. It supports use cases across digital marketing, AI development, ecommerce, and enterprise applications.\",\n      \"stats\": {\n        \"avg_execution_time_ms\": 0,\n        \"success_rate\": 0\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"dataforseo.keywords_data.google_trends.explore.live.create.v3.07aba022\",\n      \"name\": \"Setting Live ‘Google Trends Explore’ Tasks\",\n      \"description\": \"This endpoint will provide you with the keyword popularity data from the ‘Explore’ feature of Google Trends. You can check keyword trends for Google Search, Google News, Google Images, Google Shopping, and YouTube.\",\n      \"examples\": {\n        \"sample_parameters\": {\n          \"device\": \"desktop\",\n          \"date_to\": \"2024-12-31\",\n          \"keywords\": [\n            \"example keyword\"\n          ],\n          \"date_from\": \"2024-01-01\",\n          \"category_code\": 0,\n          \"location_name\": \"United States\",\n          \"time_offset_unit\": \"week\"\n        }\n      },\n      \"provider_description\": \"DataForSEO provides a comprehensive suite of APIs for SEO, keyword research, SERP data, backlinks, reviews, app stores, business listings, and more. It supports use cases across digital marketing, AI development, ecommerce, and enterprise applications.\",\n      \"stats\": {\n        \"avg_execution_time_ms\": 0,\n        \"success_rate\": 0\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"x_developer.2.likes.compliance.stream.retrieve.v1.4967071a\",\n      \"name\": \"Stream Likes compliance data\",\n      \"description\": \"Streams all compliance data related to Likes for Users.\",\n      \"params\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"backfill_minutes\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"The number of minutes of backfill requested.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"start_time\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ssZ. The earliest UTC timestamp from which the Likes Compliance events will be provided.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"end_time\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ssZ. The latest UTC timestamp from which the Likes Compliance events will be provided.\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"examples\": {\n        \"sample_parameters\": {\n          \"backfill_minutes\": 0\n        }\n      },\n      \"provider_description\": \"Use X API to fetch posts, users, trends, etc.\",\n      \"stats\": {\n        \"avg_execution_time_ms\": 0,\n        \"success_rate\": 0\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"dataforseo.keywords_data.dataforseo_trends.subregion_interests.live.v3\",\n      \"name\": \"Create DataForSEO Trends Subregion Interests Task\",\n      \"description\": \"Retrieve subregional keyword popularity data to understand how popular specified keywords are across different locations over a given time range.; This endpoint provides location-specific keyword popularity data from DataForSEO Trends. You can check keyword trends for Google Search, Google News, and Google Shopping, and compare popularity across locations and keywords.\",\n      \"examples\": {\n        \"sample_parameters\": {\n          \"keywords\": [\n            \"laptop\",\n            \"smartphone\"\n          ]\n        }\n      },\n      \"provider_description\": \"DataForSEO provides a comprehensive suite of APIs for SEO, keyword research, SERP data, backlinks, reviews, app stores, business listings, and more. It supports use cases across digital marketing, AI development, ecommerce, and enterprise applications.\",\n      \"stats\": {\n        \"avg_execution_time_ms\": 0,\n        \"success_rate\": 0\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"x_developer.2.tweets.counts.recent.retrieve.v2.3821924e\",\n      \"name\": \"Get count of recent Posts\",\n      \"description\": \"Retrieves the count of Posts from the last 7 days matching a search query.\",\n      \"params\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"query\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"One query/rule/filter for matching Posts. Refer to https://t.co/rulelength to identify the max query length.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"start_time\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ssZ. The oldest UTC timestamp (from most recent 7 days) from which the Posts will be provided. Timestamp is in second granularity and is inclusive (i.e. 12:00:01 includes the first second of the minute).\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"end_time\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ssZ. The newest, most recent UTC timestamp to which the Posts will be provided. Timestamp is in second granularity and is exclusive (i.e. 12:00:01 excludes the first second of the minute).\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"since_id\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Returns results with a Post ID greater than (that is, more recent than) the specified ID.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"until_id\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Returns results with a Post ID less than (that is, older than) the specified ID.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"next_token\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"This parameter is used to get the next 'page' of results. The value used with the parameter is pulled directly from the response provided by the API, and should not be modified.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"pagination_token\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"This parameter is used to get the next 'page' of results. The value used with the parameter is pulled directly from the response provided by the API, and should not be modified.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"granularity\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"The granularity for the search counts results.\"\n          },\n          \"enum\": [\n            \"minute\",\n            \"hour\",\n            \"day\"\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"search_count.fields\",\n          \"type\": \"array\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"A comma separated list of SearchCount fields to display.\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"examples\": {\n        \"sample_parameters\": {\n          \"query\": \"(from:TwitterDev OR from:TwitterAPI) has:media -is:retweet\"\n        }\n      },\n      \"provider_description\": \"Use X API to fetch posts, users, trends, etc.\",\n      \"stats\": {\n        \"avg_execution_time_ms\": 0,\n        \"success_rate\": 0\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"search_id\": \"a95184c5-b397-4b72-a1e8-fe65f28f2478\",\n  \"elapsed_time_ms\": 346.19\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2364,"aggregated":"{\n  \"query\": \"news popularity heat engagement metrics\",\n  \"total\": 10,\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"qveris_social.x_account_hottest_post_v1\",\n      \"name\": \"X Account Hottest Post (7 Days)\",\n      \"description\": \"Return the single hottest post (by engagement) from a given X/Twitter account in the last 7 days.\",\n      \"params\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"username\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"X/Twitter username (without @)\",\n            \"zh\": \"X账号用户名（不含@）\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"account\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Alias for username\",\n            \"zh\": \"同 username\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"provider_description\": \"Social media monitoring and analysis skills\",\n      \"skill_package_url\": \"https://qveris.ai/api/v1/skills/qveris_social.x_account_hottest_post_v1/package\",\n      \"skill_type\": \"package\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"qveris_social.x_domain_hot_topics_v1\",\n      \"name\": \"X Domain Hot Topics