{"type":"message","id":"9c74eff0","parentId":"cc1b2789","timestamp":"2026-03-03T13:36:10.277Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the results, I don't see a direct \"heat\" score in Finnhub. Let me check what the X Domain Hot Topics can provide with high engagement, which could simulate a \"heat\" metric. Or, perhaps the user's requirement of \"热度≥80\" might be something specific to their setup or a different API.\n\nSince the user specifically asked for Finnhub, let me analyze the news I got and see if there's a way to interpret \"heat\". Looking at the Finnhub data:\n- It has \"category\" - some are \"top news\" \n- The sources are MarketWatch, CNBC - major financial outlets\n\nLet me try using the X Domain Hot Topics with high min_engagement to get finance news that would have high \"heat\". I'll set min_engagement to a high value to simulate \"heat ≥ 80\".\n\nActually, let me also try to use Twitter/X social metrics to calculate engagement for the Finnhub news headlines. That could work as a proxy for \"热度\".\n\nLet me try the X hot topics with a high engagement threshold.","thinkingSignature":"222fe4849627dde5fcfe0a93e34f50243efa3ccc6866df3577338a83da51a68f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_18mnjmocpy34_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST \"https://qveris.ai/api/v1/tools/execute\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $QVERIS_API_KEY\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"tool_id\":\"qveris_social.x_domain_hot_topics_v1\",\"parameters\":{\"domains\":[\"Finance\"],\"limit\":20,\"min_engagement\":500}}' | head -500","timeout":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":38190,"output":340,"cacheRead":13984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":52514,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772544943667}}
