{"type":"message","id":"e9e73b60","parentId":"127806ef","timestamp":"2026-03-03T13:36:31.315Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The X API isn't returning data either. This might be an API key limitation. Let me try another approach - I'll use the Twitter counts API to check engagement for specific news topics.\n\nActually, thinking about this more - the user might be referring to a specific heat score that exists in a different data source, or they might have a specific definition in mind. Let me check if there are other financial news sources that might provide a \"heat\" or \"trend score\".\n\nLet me also try to work with what we have from Finnhub - maybe I can interpret \"top news\" category as high heat, or look at news that appears to be trending based on the datetime (most recent).\n\nLet me look at the Finnhub data more carefully and try to present the most important/recent news as a proxy for \"hot\" news. Or I can ask the user to clarify what they mean by \"热度\" since the Finnhub API doesn't provide this metric directly.","thinkingSignature":"c6f8f940058e0d3fcb59d4bff0676029d37e82d101e8f434e4301e2cbf39251e"},{"type":"text","text":"The X/Twitter API isn't returning data (likely quota/permissions issue). Let me check if there's another way to get trending scores. Let me also check the current Finnhub news we retrieved and see if we can identify high-impact news:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_q1et1c7s6283_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST \"https://qveris.ai/api/v1/tools/execute\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $QVERIS_API_KEY\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"tool_id\":\"finnhub.market.news.list.v1\",\"parameters\":{\"category\":\"general\"}}' | python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\ndata = json.load(sys.stdin)\nif 'result' in data and data['result'].get('data'):\n    articles = data['result']['data']\n    # Sort by datetime (newest first)\n    articles.sort(key=lambda x: x.get('datetime', 0), reverse=True)\n    print('=== Latest Finnhub Market News ===')\n    print(f'Total: {len(articles)} articles\\n')\n    for i, a in enumerate(articles[:15]):\n        dt = a.get('datetime', 0)\n        from datetime import datetime\n        dt_str = datetime.fromtimestamp(dt).strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M') if dt else 'N/A'\n        print(f'{i+1}. [{dt_str}] {a.get(\\\"headline\\\", \\\"N/A\\\")[:80]}')\n        print(f'   Source: {a.get(\\\"source\\\", \\\"N/A\\\")}')\n        print()\n\"","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":38694,"output":551,"cacheRead":13984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":53229,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772544976056}}
